quran[8]{c,v,t,f}:
2,94,"Say to them: “If indeed the Last Abode with Allah is yours, in exclusion of other people, then long for death {1} if you are truthful.”",footnotes:1:This is a subtle
2,95,"But they shall never long for it because of the (evil) deeds they have committed; Allah is well aware of the wrong-doers."
2,96,"You will certainly find them most eager to cling on to life, {1} indeed even more eager than those who associate others with Allah in His Divinity. Each one of them wishes to live a thousand years although the bestowal of long life cannot remove him from chastisement. Allah sees whatever they do.",footnotes:1:The Arabic text implies that the Jews were so frightened of death and so keen to remain alive that they did not mind whether they led an honourable and dignified existence
2,97,"Say: “Whoever is an enemy to Gabriel {1} (should know that) he revealed this (Qur’an) to your heart by Allah’s {2} leave: it confirms the Scriptures revealed before it, {3} and is a guidance and good tiding to the people of faith. {4}",footnotes:1:The Jews not only reviled the Prophet (peace be on him) and his followers but also God's chosen angel
2,98,"(And if this is the cause of their hostility to Gabriel, let them know) whoever is an enemy to Allah, His Angels and His Messengers and to Gabriel and Michael will surely find Allah an enemy to such unbelievers.”"
2,99,"We surely sent down to you clear verses that elucidate the Truth, (verses) which only the transgressors reject as false."
2,100,"Is it not that every time they made a covenant with Allah a party of them set it aside? The truth is that most of them do not truly believe."
2,101,"And whenever a Messenger from Allah came to them, confirming what they already possessed, a party of those who had been given the Scripture flung the Book of Allah behind their backs as if they knew nothing,"
